        <h2>Why We Built This</h2>
        <p>We believe every high school athlete deserves a celebration that honors their hard work, dedication, and team spirit. But we noticed a problem: there was no single, trusted resource for planning high school sports banquets and celebrations.</p>
        <p>Coaches were piecing together ideas from Pinterest, asking other coaches for advice, and spending too much time on planning when they could be focusing on their athletes. Booster club parents were reinventing the wheel every season.</p>
        <p>So we built this.</p>

        <h2>What Makes This Different</h2>
        <p>Every guide, checklist, and resource on this site has been developed with input from high school coaches, athletic directors, booster club leaders, and event planners who have organized hundreds of athletic celebrations. We don't just give you ideas — we give you systems that work.</p>
        <p>This isn't a store. It's a library of practical, field-tested planning resources built specifically for high school athletics.</p>

        <h2>Our Story</h2>
        <p>SportsBanquetGuide.com is brought to you by Lakeshore Gift, a company that started with a simple observation: banquet table centerpieces for high school sports events were either generic or expensive. We saw an opportunity to create custom 3D printed sports centerpieces that truly captured the spirit of high school athletics — at a price that made sense for school budgets.</p>
        <p>Today, we produce centerpieces for football, basketball, soccer, volleyball, cheerleading, track & field, hockey, and more — each one crafted to a team's specific sport and colors.</p>

        <h2>What We Offer</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Comprehensive planning guides</strong> — For every type of athletic celebration</li>
          <li><strong>Downloadable checklists and templates</strong> — Print-ready resources</li>
          <li><strong>Decoration ideas</strong> — From budget-friendly to premium</li>
          <li><strong>Product recommendations</strong> — Only what we'd use ourselves</li>
        </ul>

